{
  "stem": "11998.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If you were caught-- we were wearing, of course, the armband or the Star of David and the Judenstern, as they call it.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if you were caught outside, they would deport you.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And nobody knew what would happen to you once you were deported.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there were, there were-- not that I remember that there were any shooting or anything of that nature going on in Czestochowa-- I mean, in Sosnowiec--",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At that time.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there were two, two.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At first, we had the-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I don't remember which one was first.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think the Star of David was the first one that we wore, a yellow star with Jude on it, what means Jew.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we wore it on the, on the left, left side.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I don't remember whether it was later or, or earlier that we wore white bands with a blue Star of David.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I think that the band came first and then the, and then the Star of David.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, they did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A lot of people did.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were caught.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They would be either interrogated or beaten.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I know-- I remember one of my neighbors was almost killed by being caught outside the area where he's supposed to be.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he was accused of smuggling or being a black marketeer.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they, they almost killed him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They certainly made him a cripple.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that was, that was about the only thing that we heard.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There was a lady, a German woman, that lived from-- that came from Germany, a Jewish woman whose husband was taken from her and sent to a camp or, or even murdered.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
